headline: Subaru Selects HPE to Accelerate AI Development for Next-Generation Eyesight Driver Assist System
summary: TOKYO, July 28, 2025--HPE (NYSE: HPE) today announced that Subaru selected HPE Cray XD670 servers to orchestrate its image recognition technology and AI. This rollout supports Subaru’s vision of increasing customer value and improving preventive safety—one of the key pillars of the car manufacturer’s comprehensive philosophy. headline: Tines Appoints Heather Planishek as Chief Operating and Financial Officer
summary: Tines, the intelligent workflow platform for security and IT teams, today announced the appointment of Heather Planishek as its Chief Operating and Financial Officer (COFO).
